  <!-- LESSON 3b: Dark Mode & Checklist               -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section id="dark-mode-checklist" data-slide-index="2" data-lesson-slug="accessibility-requirements" class="module-section py-16">
    <h3 id="dark-mode-accessibility">Dark mode accessibility</h3>

    <p>
      Dark mode introduces specific accessibility challenges. Key rules:
    </p>

    <div class="list-card">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Muted text on dark backgrounds</strong> — neutral_500 (#6B6B8A) on neutral_900 (#1A1A2E) only achieves 3.33:1. This passes for large text but fails for normal text. Use muted text sparingly in dark mode and only at 18px+ or 14px+ bold.</li>
        <li><strong>Status colors</strong> — always use dark text on chromatic status backgrounds (success, warning, danger, info), in both light and dark mode. Never use white text on these colors.</li>
        <li><strong>Images</strong> — reduce brightness to 85-90% to prevent glare on dark backgrounds.</li>
        <li><strong>Tier 2 pages always render in light mode</strong> — dark mode can feel isolating in crisis contexts.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 id="the-playbook-accessibility-checklist">The Playbook accessibility checklist</h3>

    <p>
      Run through this before any content ships:
    </p>

    <div class="my-6 rounded-xl border border-n100 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
      <div class="bg-navy px-4 py-3">
        <span class="text-xs font-heading font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-teal">Pre-Ship Checklist</span>
        <p class="text-white font-heading font-bold text-sm mt-0.5">Accessibility Requirements</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4">
        <p class="text-xs font-heading font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-n400 mb-2">Visual & Contrast</p>
        <div class="space-y-1 mb-4">
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 p-2.5 rounded-lg hover:bg-n50 transition-colors cursor-pointer">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-0.5 w-4 h-4 rounded border-2 border-n300 text-teal accent-[#00D4AA] flex-shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-sm text-navy"><strong>Contrast ratios verified</strong> — every text/background combination meets 4.5:1 (normal) or 3:1 (large)</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 p-2.5 rounded-lg hover:bg-n50 transition-colors cursor-pointer">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-0.5 w-4 h-4 rounded border-2 border-n300 text-teal accent-[#00D4AA] flex-shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-sm text-navy"><strong>Touch targets measured</strong> — all interactive elements are 44x44px minimum</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 p-2.5 rounded-lg hover:bg-n50 transition-colors cursor-pointer">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-0.5 w-4 h-4 rounded border-2 border-n300 text-teal accent-[#00D4AA] flex-shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-sm text-navy"><strong>No color-only information</strong> — meaning is conveyed by text, icons, or patterns alongside color</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 p-2.5 rounded-lg hover:bg-n50 transition-colors cursor-pointer">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-0.5 w-4 h-4 rounded border-2 border-n300 text-teal accent-[#00D4AA] flex-shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-sm text-navy"><strong>Helpline numbers in Source Code Pro</strong> — 0/O and 1/l/I character disambiguation verified</span>
          </label>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs font-heading font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-n400 mb-2">Interaction & Devices</p>
        <div class="space-y-1">
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 p-2.5 rounded-lg hover:bg-n50 transition-colors cursor-pointer">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-0.5 w-4 h-4 rounded border-2 border-n300 text-teal accent-[#00D4AA] flex-shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-sm text-navy"><strong>Keyboard tested</strong> — every action can be completed without a mouse</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 p-2.5 rounded-lg hover:bg-n50 transition-colors cursor-pointer">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-0.5 w-4 h-4 rounded border-2 border-n300 text-teal accent-[#00D4AA] flex-shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-sm text-navy"><strong>Screen reader tested</strong> — content makes sense when read linearly</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 p-2.5 rounded-lg hover:bg-n50 transition-colors cursor-pointer">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-0.5 w-4 h-4 rounded border-2 border-n300 text-teal accent-[#00D4AA] flex-shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-sm text-navy"><strong>Alt text on all images</strong> — descriptive for informational images, empty for decorative</span>
          </label>
          <label class="flex items-start gap-3 p-2.5 rounded-lg hover:bg-n50 transition-colors cursor-pointer">
            <input type="checkbox" class="mt-0.5 w-4 h-4 rounded border-2 border-n300 text-teal accent-[#00D4AA] flex-shrink-0" />
            <span class="text-sm text-navy"><strong>Responsive tested</strong> — works on mobile, tablet, desktop, and assistive devices</span>
          </label>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

