  <!-- LESSON 3c: Accessibility Exercise              -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section id="accessibility-exercise" data-slide-index="2" data-lesson-slug="accessibility-requirements" data-has-exercise class="module-section py-16">
    <h3 id="practice-spot-the-failures">Practice: spot the failures</h3>

    <p>
      Apply what you've learned. Each layout below has accessibility issues — see how many you can identify.
    </p>

    <AccessibilityChecker client:visible />

    <KeyTakeaway>
      <p>
        Accessibility is especially important for Playbook because the people most likely to need help are also most likely to be in stressful situations where cognitive load is high and patience is low. Accessible design isn't charity — it's effective design.
      </p>
    </KeyTakeaway>

    <GenerativeExercise
      client:visible
      title="Write a Tier 2 Support Page Brief"
      prompt="A player clicks 'I need help' on your operator's app. Write a design brief (3–5 sentences) describing what the support landing page should look like. Apply the Tier 2 visual rules you learned: no decoration, maximum white space, light mode only, clear hierarchy, and zero friction to resources."
      placeholder="Describe the visual design of the support landing page…"
      rubric={[
        'Specifies light mode only — no dark mode for Tier 2',
        'Describes a minimal layout with generous white space',
        'Removes all decorative elements and branding flair',
        'Prioritizes helpline number and self-exclusion link above the fold',
        'Mentions accessibility requirements (contrast, font size, touch targets)',
      ]}
      modelAnswer="The support page opens in forced light mode with a white background and maximum white space. No decorative elements, no brand illustrations, no orange accent — only navy text on white with the teal helpline number as the sole color accent. The helpline number and 'Pause your account' button sit above the fold at minimum 18px type, with 48px touch targets. Layout is a single centered column — no sidebar, no navigation distractions. Every link opens in the same window. The entire page loads in under 1 second with zero JavaScript dependencies."
    />
  </section>

